title: ICE: rustdoc: `failed to fully process`

labels.name: T-rustdoc
labels.description: Relevant to the rustdoc team, which will review and decide on the PR/issue.

labels.name: I-ICE
labels.description: Issue: The compiler panicked, giving an Internal Compilation Error (ICE) ❄️

labels.name: T-compiler
labels.description: Relevant to the compiler team, which will review and decide on the PR/issue.

labels.name: A-synthetic-impls
labels.description: Area: Synthetic impls, used by rustdoc to document auto traits and traits with blanket impls

body:
### Code ```Rust pub struct Inner<'a, T: 'a> { field: &'a T, } trait MyTrait { type MyItem; } trait OtherTrait {} unsafe impl<'a, T> Send for Inner<'a, T> where 'a: 'static, T: MyTrait, { } unsafe impl<'a, T> Sync for Inner<'a, T> where 'a: 'static, T: MyTrait, ::MyItem: OtherTrait, { } pub struct Foo<'c, K: 'c> { inner_field: Inner<'c, K>, } ``` ### Meta `rustc --version --verbose`: ``` ``` ### Error output ``` rustdoc 1.71.0-nightly (b628260df 2023-04-22) binary: rustdoc commit-hash: b628260df0587ae559253d8640ecb8738d3de613 commit-date: 2023-04-22 host: x86_64-unknown-linux-gnu release: 1.71.0-nightly LLVM version: 16.0.2 ```
